  "prompt": "Does the law differentiate between intentional and unintentional money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, in most legal systems, there is a distinction between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering typically involves deliberate actions to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds, while unintentional money laundering may occur through negligence or lack of proper due diligence. The penalties and legal consequences can vary significantly based on the intent and circumstances.\n\nIntentional money laundering usually carries more severe criminal penalties, while unintentional money laundering might result in civil penalties or administrative actions. However, specific details can vary by jurisdiction.",
